this place is spic and span.

02:15.712 --> 02:18.147
Yeah, I guess that would
make Garrity span.

02:18.215 --> 02:19.248
Ha!

02:19.317 --> 02:21.383
Hey, guys. Where are we?

02:21.452 --> 02:23.549
Yeah, it's either the
twilight zone or hell.

02:23.669 --> 02:27.523
Firefighter Gavin, firefighter
Shea, you are both late.

02:27.592 --> 02:29.659
Hell.

02:29.728 --> 02:31.728
Sorry, big man.
No smoking in the house.

02:31.796 --> 02:32.562
It's not even lit.

02:32.630 --> 02:34.197
Yeah, well, all the same,
it's against the protocols

02:34.265 --> 02:36.632
of your new fitness regimen,
cupcake, details

02:36.701 --> 02:41.003
of which are posted in your locker. I expect
a signed copy on my desk within the hour.

02:41.072 --> 02:42.071
Oh, your desk.

02:42.140 --> 02:43.939
This is the way Needles
explained this whole thing to me--

02:44.008 --> 02:48.778
He's on day 2 of a 5-day
term as the interim lieutenant.

02:48.847 --> 02:50.362
It's only the tip of the iceberg, you know.

02:50.482 --> 02:53.951
I don't think this guy's eaten, slept, or
even pissed in 72 hours.

02:54.020 --> 02:55.787
Well, chief, I think it's just
a testament to what a man

02:55.855 --> 02:57.376
can do when he puts his mind to something.

02:57.496 --> 03:00.458
Speaking of which, why don't you follow
suit and get dressed. We got work to do.

03:02.562 --> 03:04.262
That means you, too, Fonzie.

03:04.331 --> 03:05.129
Hey!

03:05.198 --> 03:08.099
Heyyyy... no more kicking around
the house, drinking coffee in your

03:08.168 --> 03:11.269
motorcycle boots and your leather
jacket, slick. Station gear at all times.

03:11.337 --> 03:13.004
Frankie--I'm sorry.

03:13.072 --> 03:15.606
Lieutenant, I think I'm gonna
rub the paint off the door

03:15.675 --> 03:16.918
