Can I do something else?

03:17.038 --> 03:18.433
Well, did you hit those
couple spots I pointed out?

03:18.553 --> 03:19.543
Yeah, I got 'em.

03:19.611 --> 03:23.179
All right, then carry on, firefighter
Garrity, but tuck your shirt in first.

03:23.248 --> 03:25.214
- You serious?
- Do I look like I'm kidding?

03:25.283 --> 03:26.983
You look like you're about to
squeeze a diamond out of your

03:27.052 --> 03:29.052
ass is what you look like.

03:29.120 --> 03:30.987
Garrity, I think just for that,
you ought to hit that door

03:31.056 --> 03:32.769
one more time, asshole.

03:36.027 --> 03:37.570
We've really--we gotta
put up with this?

03:37.690 --> 03:40.931
Don't look at me now.
This is Lou's brilliant idea.

03:40.999 --> 03:42.799
Now I know how Mary Shelley felt.

03:42.868 --> 03:44.634
Mm-hmm. Francostein.

03:44.703 --> 03:46.269
Mmm, very funny.

03:46.338 --> 03:48.438
I guess now the only question is
is Lou gonna stand by his word,

03:48.507 --> 03:51.140
or are you gonna bitch
out and pull rank?

03:51.209 --> 03:52.275
How many calls you had?

03:52.344 --> 03:53.676
Been a few.

03:53.745 --> 03:58.047
A few false alarms, a couple of medicals.
Rivera's been riding along.

03:58.116 --> 03:59.581
Riding along.

03:59.650 --> 04:00.482
Hee hee hee.

04:01.852 --> 04:03.285
Something funny?

04:03.354 --> 04:06.255
Yeah, good old ride-along Rivera.

04:06.323 --> 04:08.399
No, no, this is all good, but
you know what,

04:08.519 --> 04:12.262
