was, a man so brave that

14:34.065 --> 14:37.467
I felt safe no matter what the
circumstance might be each time

14:37.535 --> 14:39.509
you led us off that rig.

14:40.106 --> 14:41.866
All the praise and all the glory I was

14:41.986 --> 14:45.576
given for my so-called heroics
only existed because I knew

14:45.645 --> 14:50.264
no matter what that you were just a
few steps away ready,

14:50.384 --> 14:53.618
willing, and able to pull me to safety.

14:53.686 --> 14:57.155
I rest in peace now knowing that
my family will forever be

14:57.224 --> 15:00.192
in your warm, protective embrace.

15:00.261 --> 15:04.096
See you on the other side, my brother.
Love, Tommy.

15:05.033 --> 15:09.487
P.S. Don't let Janet
sleep with Franco."

